# Shana, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Shana (; , Shanaa) is a rural locality (an ulus) in Selenginsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 267 as of 2010. There are 5 streets.
Geography
Shana is located 53&nbsp;km southwest of Gusinoozyorsk (the district's administrative centre) by road. Selenduma is the nearest rural locality.
